The ICE Lab presented our latest work on time-interleaved SAR ADC design at the IEEE International Solid-State Circuits Conference (ISSCC) 2026 in San Francisco.

## Paper Summary

Our paper, "A 12-bit 1-GS/s Time-Interleaved SAR ADC with Background Calibration in 28nm CMOS," demonstrates a novel background calibration technique that achieves state-of-the-art SNDR performance while maintaining low power consumption.

### Key Results

- **Resolution:** 12 bits
- **Sampling Rate:** 1 GS/s
- **SNDR:** 62.5 dB
- **Power:** 45 mW
- **Technology:** 28nm CMOS

## Presentation

Alex Chen presented the work during the Data Converter session. The presentation was well received, with several groups expressing interest in collaboration.

We thank NSF for supporting this research through the CAREER award program.
